South African President Jacob Zuma's own African National Congress (ANC) party decided to remove him from office as head of state in the early hours of Tuesday, according to reports in several local media outlets. Reports from inside the party's National Executive Committee, which met for 13 hours from Monday into Tuesday at a hotel outside of Pretoria to discuss Zuma's future, suggest officials have given him 48 hours to step down. It follows weeks of speculation over his future. Read more: South Africa's President Zuma: A chronology of scandal Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
